@NODE "History"

@{JCENTER}@{B}@{U}CheckHDParts - History@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
@{B}@{B}V1.02 - 30 Apr 98@{UB}

      - I was reminded that some hard drives do not have device/partition
        names starting with "DH" so I removed the search for "DH" and
        instead filtered out device names such as RAM: RAD: DFx: and
        displayed all the others, leaving it up to the user to decide
        whether to include the device name in the monitoring process.

        My thanks to Richie Burke, who has an AmiQuest drive with partition
        names AQx:, for this reminder. Find him at:-

        R.Burke-97@student.lboro.ac.uk
        http://www-student.lboro.ac.uk/~corb1/life.html
        http://www-student.lboro.ac.uk/~corb1/music.html
        http://www-student.lboro.ac.uk/~corb1/index.html (for Amiga users)

@{B}V1.01 - 03 Apr 98@{UB} - First public release

